cat << EOF
HexChat is an IRC client based on XChat. HexChat was originally called XChat-WDK
which in turn was a successor of freakschat.
Features - Easy to use and customizable interface - Cross-platform on Windows,
OS X, and Unix-like OSes - Highly scriptable with Python and Perl - Translated
in multiple languages - Fully open source and actively developed - Multi-network
with auto-connect, join, and identify - Spellcheck, Proxies, SASL, DCC support
and more
EOF
